Brokers in ZooKeeper mode
Authoritative metadata lives in ZooKeeper znodes (/brokers, /topics, /config, /controller, etc.).
Write path (create topic, alter partitions, etc.)-- Admin client → any broker(CreateTopics, CreatePartitions) --broker-->current controller Controller validates and does all ZooKeeper writes
Controller broadcasts new metadata to brokers(LeaderAndIsr / UpdateMetadata RPCs to all brokers.)--> broker updates its in‑memory metadata cache
Read path (DescribeTopics, Metadata, etc.)..Brokers read from in‑memory metadata cache.--> The Cache is kept up‑to‑date by the controller’s UpdateMetadata RPCs and controller changes, not by hitting ZK per request.



